Body: Description: When we try to Print a document having Canadian SIN number , the policy violation Alert is not generate at EPP console .
Next Steps Updated: I received log files in an email and after I test it some more I will open an R&D ticket
What We've Learned Updated: testing on the support side, we can see that ssn is not even triggering when DPI is turned on. Printing still does not trigger at all. Further tests are needed
Next Steps Updated: Engineering is still investigating after the logs were provided.

What We've Learned Updated: It appears the examples used by the customer do not match the implemented detection rules, so I asked for clarifications for future cases and samples that do work with our rules.
Next Steps Updated: waiting for engineering to provide samples and explanation of the detection process.
What We've Learned Updated: the customer will test some more with the valid test numbers and take it from there
Next Steps Updated: waiting on the customer to test with a larger test pool and close the case if the result is positive
What We've Learned Updated: in the meeting today we tested with some other SIN numbers generated and it worked as intended
Next Steps Updated: will talk about it in our meeting tomorrow and maybe close it
Next Steps Updated: the customer will go live since we managed to successfully test it out. waiting for a few days to make sure everything works.
